<Link id="l00230" /><CodeLine lineNumber="230"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Pin one of the tagged slots to offset 0 from the tagged base pointer.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00231" /><CodeLine lineNumber="231"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This would make its address available in a virtual register (IRG&#39;s def), as</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00232" /><CodeLine lineNumber="232"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// opposed to requiring an ADDG instruction to materialize. This effectively</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00233" /><CodeLine lineNumber="233"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// eliminates a vreg (by replacing it with direct uses of IRG, which is usually</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00234" /><CodeLine lineNumber="234"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// live almost everywhere anyway), and therefore needs to happen before</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00235" /><CodeLine lineNumber="235"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// regalloc.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00236" /><CodeLine lineNumber="236" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-aarch64stacktaggingprera-cpp-/aarch64stacktaggingprera/#a7e7be476481e8e24c35c332a9e6e26ad"><span class="doxyHighlight">std::optional&lt;int&gt; <a href="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-aarch64stacktaggingprera-cpp-/aarch64stacktaggingprera/#a7e7be476481e8e24c35c332a9e6e26ad">AArch64StackTaggingPreRA::findFirstSlotCandidate</a>() &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00237" /><CodeLine lineNumber="237"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Find the best (FI, Tag) pair to pin to offset 0</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00238" /><CodeLine lineNumber="238"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Looking at the possible uses of a tagged address, the advantage of pinning</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00239" /><CodeLine lineNumber="239"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// is:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00240" /><CodeLine lineNumber="240"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - COPY to physical register.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00241" /><CodeLine lineNumber="241"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   Does not matter, this would trade a MOV instruction for an ADDG.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00242" /><CodeLine lineNumber="242"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - ST&#42;G matter, but those mostly appear near the function prologue where all</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00243" /><CodeLine lineNumber="243"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   the tagged addresses need to be materialized anyway; also, counting ST&#42;G</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00244" /><CodeLine lineNumber="244"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   uses would overweight large allocas that require more than one ST&#42;G</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00245" /><CodeLine lineNumber="245"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   instruction.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00246" /><CodeLine lineNumber="246"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - Load/Store instructions in the address operand do not require a tagged</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00247" /><CodeLine lineNumber="247"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   pointer, so they also do not benefit. These operands have already been</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00248" /><CodeLine lineNumber="248"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   eliminated (see uncheckLoadsAndStores) so all remaining load/store</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00249" /><CodeLine lineNumber="249"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   instructions count.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00250" /><CodeLine lineNumber="250"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - Any other instruction may benefit from being pinned to offset 0</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00251" /><CodeLine lineNumber="251"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/debug-h/#a196897517069dda1bdb549e24468f7d7">LLVM&#95;DEBUG</a>(<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a7c46c742c31be54870e2038048e6b391">dbgs</a>() &lt;&lt; </span><span class="doxyHighlightStringLiteral">&quot;AArch64StackTaggingPreRA::findFirstSlotCandidate\\n&quot;</span><span class="doxyHighlight">);</span></CodeLine>
